         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>l. 1,  Whatever stood at the beginning of the line—the outline suggests a cross—has been deeply erased.</p>
            <p>l. 7,  The <foreign xml:lang="grc">Α</foreign> at the end of the line, which conforms to the other letters, might be a numeral or a false start in writing <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀνέθηκεν</foreign>.</p>
            <p>1.9: The <foreign xml:lang="grc">Α</foreign> is very roughly written, and has the appearance of a rough graffito addition.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>The splendid and well-known metropolis of the Aphrodisians set up <supplied reason="subaudible">this statue of</supplied> Bitianos, <term xml:lang="la">clarissimus scholasticus</term> and consular, their own benefactor and agonothete.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="V.38" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
